<HEADLINE>
FT  24 OCT 92 / Markets: Cheer for smaller companies - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Small company shares joined in the general euphoria of the equity market
this week, as the government emphasised its plans to 'go for growth'. The
County Small Companies Index rose 1.8 per cent to 831.03 (815.94) over the
week to October 22, while the Hoare Govett Index (capital gains version)
rose 2 per cent from 1054.6 to 1075.56 over the same period.
</TEXT>
